net.opentsdb.query.expression

类 EDPtoDPS

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.opentsdb.query.expression.EDPtoDPS
  • 所有已实现的接口:
    Iterable<DataPoint>, DataPoints

    public class EDPtoDPS
extends Object
implements DataPoints
    An ugly temporary class for converting from an expression datapoint to a standard data point for serialization in the default query format.

      • getAggregatedTags

        public List<String> getAggregatedTags()
        从接口复制的说明: DataPoints
        Returns the tags associated with some but not all of the data points.

        When this instance represents the aggregation of multiple time series (same metric but different tags), DataPoints.getTags() returns the tags that are common to all data points (intersection set) whereas this method returns all the tags names that are not common to all data points (union set minus the intersection set, also called the symmetric difference).

        If this instance does not represent an aggregation of multiple time series, the list returned is empty.

        指定者:
        getAggregatedTags 在接口中 DataPoints
        返回:
        A non-null list of tag names.

        指定者:

        返回:

      • aggregatedSize

        public int aggregatedSize()
        从接口复制的说明: DataPoints
        Returns the number of data points aggregated in this instance.

        When this instance represents the aggregation of multiple time series (same metric but different tags), DataPoints.size() returns the number of data points after aggregation, whereas this method returns the number of data points before aggregation.

        If this instance does not represent an aggregation of multiple time series, then 0 is returned.

        指定者:
        aggregatedSize 在接口中 DataPoints
        返回:
        A positive integer.

      • iterator

        public SeekableView iterator()
        从接口复制的说明: DataPoints
        Returns a zero-copy view to go through size() data points.

        The iterator returned must return each DataPoint in O(1). The DataPoint returned must not be stored and gets invalidated as soon as next is called on the iterator. If you want to store individual data points, you need to copy the timestamp and value out of each DataPoint into your own data structures.

        指定者:
        iterator 在接口中 Iterable<DataPoint>
        指定者:
        iterator 在接口中 DataPoints

      • timestamp

        public long timestamp(int i)
        从接口复制的说明: DataPoints
        Returns the timestamp associated with the ith data point. The first data point has index 0.

        This method must be implemented in O(DataPoints.aggregatedSize()) or better.

        It is guaranteed that 

        timestamp(i) < timestamp(i+1)
        指定者:
        timestamp 在接口中 DataPoints
        返回:
        A strictly positive integer.
